### Google Auth Integration Testing

## 1. Test Google Authentication Endpoint

### Create a new user via Google
POST http://localhost:3333/auth/google
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "YOUR_GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE"
}

### Notes for Testing:
# 1. Get a Google Access Token:
#    - Visit: https://developers.google.com/oauthplayground
#    - Select Google OAuth 2.0 APIs > Gmail API v1 or any API
#    - Click "Authorize APIs"
#    - Copy the access_token from the response
#
# 2. Replace YOUR_GOOGLE_ACCESS_TOKEN_HERE with the actual token
#
# 3. Expected Response:
#    {
#      "user": {
#        "id": "uuid-string",
#        "name": "User Name",
#        "email": "user@example.com",
#        "picture": "https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/..."
#      },
#      "token": "jwt.token.here"
#    }

---

## 2. Test Authenticated Endpoint with JWT

### Get current user info
GET http://localhost:3333/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN_HERE

### Notes:
# - Use the "token" value from the Google auth response
# - Expected Response: User object with all fields

---

## 3. Test Traditional Login (existing users)

### Login with email/password
POST http://localhost:3333/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

---

## 4. Test Registration (fallback)

### Register a new user
POST http://localhost:3333/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "name": "John Doe",
  "email": "john@example.com",
  "password": "SecurePassword123"
}

